HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 247
By McCalmon
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the board, staff, and
volunteers of the Williamson County Fair.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those events that promote local business, entertain and educate our citizens, and celebrate the
history and culture of the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, the Williamson County Fair is one such estimable event, which recently
received the prestigious honor of being named the Division AAA State Champion Fair in the
Merit Award Competition of the Tennessee Association of Fairs at their recent annual
convention and also earned multiple first-place awards for marketing and promotional efforts;
and
WHEREAS, winning national acclaim at the International Association of Fairs and
Expositions Awards, the Williamson County Fair received top honors for Sponsorship Innovation
with the American Flag Display, presented by The Gary Sinise Foundation; and
WHEREAS, in addition, the Williamson County Fair has been named a top-three finalist
in the Festival/Fair category at the Official Community's Choice Awards - Best of Music City, a
testament to its reputation as one of Middle Tennessee's most cherished events; and
WHEREAS, the Williamson County Fair greatly benefits from the stalwart leadership of
manager Matt "Cowboy" Buchanan, a host of dedicated volunteers, and unwavering community
support; and
WHEREAS, the success of the Williamson County Fair and its well-earned recognition
bring great pride to the people of Williamson County, who every year unite with tireless
dedication to celebrate and promote local business, agriculture, and history with this time-
honored event; now, therefore,
